From the back of the 2008 card:

The HW40 was designed by Jun Imai. As a child, Imai never imagined he would end up working alongside Larry Wood, who designed Imai's very first Hot Wheels car, the Dixie Challenger. In designing the HW40, Imai made it fit for drag, drift, road course, or trips to the toy store. The jet turbine engine, seamless body, and one-piece "glass" hood and windshield make this Designer's Challenge winner look bold, aggressive, and muscular
